1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact sections 37-17.1-22, 37-17.1-23, and 37-17.1-27 of the
2 North Dakota Century Code, relating to disaster or emergency response and recovery costs,
3 authority to spend funds from the state disaster relief fund, and uses of the state disaster relief
4 fund.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
6 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 37-17.1-22 of the North Dakota Century Code is
7 amended and reenacted as follows:
8 37-17.1-22. Disaster or emergency response and recovery costs.
9 Whenever the governor declares a state of disaster or emergency in accordance with
10 section 37-17.1-05, or when the governor enters into an agreement with the federal government
11 following a disaster or emergency declared by the president of the United States, the director of
12 the division of homeland security shall determine and record the costs of the state response
13 and recovery operations in accordance with an agreement with the federal government or in
14 accordance with procedures established by the governor in the case of a state-declared
15 disaster or emergency. Immediately following the response or recovery operations, or prior
16 thereto if determined necessary by the governor, the governor may apply to the state
17 emergency commission for a grant of funds in an amount equal to the response and recovery
18 costs of the state to be paid from the state disaster relief fund or other funds approved by the
19 emergency commission. Notwithstanding other provisions of chapter 54-16, it must be
20 conclusively presumed upon receipt by the emergency commission of the application from the
21 governor that a disaster or emergency exists, and the commission may grant and direct the
22 transfer to the department of the governor designated representative of an amount up to that
23 certified in the application by the governor.
