1 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 37-17.1-23 of the North Dakota Century Code is
2 amended and reenacted as follows:
3 37-17.1-23. Disaster or emergency recovery funding - Loan authorization.
4 1. When approved by the emergency commission, the office of the adjutant general is
5 authorized to borrow from the Bank of North Dakota, to match federal funds under the
6 Robert T. Stafford Disaster Emergency Assistance Act [Public Law 93-288, as
7 amended]. In addition to the principal repayment, the Bank of North Dakota shall
8 receive interest on the loan at a rate equal to other state agency borrowings. On
9 behalf of the state, the office of the adjutant general shall administer the disaster or
10 emergency recovery program according to state procedures based on federal laws or
11 regulations. After a county or group of counties have been declared a major disaster or
12 emergency area by the president, the office of the adjutant general shall submit a
13 request to the emergency commission for:
14 a. Approval to make an application for a loan from the Bank of North Dakota;
15 b. Approval for additional personnel required to perform the anticipated recovery
16 activities; and
17 c. Authority to spend additional state and federal funds for the recovery program;
18 and
19 d. Authority to spend available funds from the state disaster relief fund.
20 2. If the request is acceptable, the emergency commission shall approve the request and
21 issue a notice of its action to the office of the adjutant general, Bank of North Dakota,
22 and the office of management and budget. The office of the adjutant general shall
23 keep the emergency commission apprised of the progress of the recovery operation
24 and submit a final report upon completion of the project. The office of the adjutant
25 general is responsible to repay any loan, including accrued interest, from the Bank of
26 North Dakota which is provided under this section. If at the end of the biennium a
27 balance exists on the loan, the office of the adjutant general shall request the
28 legislative assembly for a deficiency appropriation to repay the loan.
